  "prompt": "What is the coefficient of Friction value for turcite on steel and turcite on turcite?",
  "response": "Turcite, a type of engineered plastic, is commonly used as a bearing material. The coefficient of friction can vary depending on specific formulations and conditions, but general values can be provided.\n\n1. **Turcite on Steel**: The coefficient of friction for Turcite on steel typically ranges from **0.1 to 0.2** (static) and about **0.05 to 0.1** (dynamic).\n\n2. **Turcite on Turcite**: When Turcite is sliding on itself, the coefficient of friction usually ranges from **0.1 to 0.15** (static) and about **0.05 to 0.1** (dynamic).\n\nThese values can vary based on factors such as surface finish, lubrication, and operational conditions, so it's always advisable to refer to the manufacturer's specifications for the most accurate and applicable values for specific applications.",
